-   Gas is assumed to consist of a very large number of molecules that have identical and negligible size.
-   Molecules move around randomly
-   Collisions between molecules and within containing walls are elastic
-   Average KE of gas molecules is directly proportional to absolute temp (kelvin)
-   Laws
$$
\frac{pv}{t} = constant
$$$$
\frac{p_{1}v_{1}}{t_{1}} = \frac{p_{2}v_{2}}{t_{2}} 
$$

-   Pressure Law 
$$
p \propto t
$$
-   Boyle Law
$$
p \propto \frac{1}{v}
$$
-   Charles Law
$$
v \propto t
$$
-   Avogadro Law ![](data:image/png;base64,)

$$
n \propto v
$$
$$
\frac{pv}{nT} = R \approx 8.31
$$
-   Universal Gas constant
$$
8.31jk^{-1}mol^{-1}
$$
